ExecDesc.value: Apple iTunes m3u Playlist Multiple Buffer Overflows(IPv6)

EngDesc.value: Multiple buffer overflows have been discovered in Apple iTunes. The vulnerabilities are located in the code responsible for handling m3u files and can be triggered by overly long records in m3u files. An attacker can exploit this vulnerability by enticing a user to open an m3u file with iTunes or to view a specially crafted web page with an embedded m3u playlist. Successful exploitation could result in arbitrary code execution in the context of the currently logged in user.
